<div id="main">
  <h1 id="title">Jon Snow</h1>
  <div id="img-div">
    <img id="image" src="https://cdn1.thr.com/sites/default/files/imagecache/scale_crop_768_433/2017/08/helen_sloan_-_hbo_photo_43_-_h_2017.jpg" alt="Pelley with Darfur refugees, 2006"/>
    <p id="img-caption">Jon Snow, 'Beyond The Wall'</p>
  </div>
  <div id="tribute-info">
    <ul>
      <li>Jon Snow is a fictional character in the A Song of Ice and Fire series of fantasy novels by American author George R. R. Martin, and its television adaptation Game of Thrones, in which he is portrayed by Kit Harington.</li>
      <li>Jon is introduced in 1996's A Game of Thrones as the illegitimate son of Ned Stark, the honorable lord of Winterfell, an ancient fortress in the North of the fictional continent of Westeros</li>
      <li>Jon finds himself honor bound to remain with the Watch.</li>
      <li>Jon returns as a prominent character in a A Dance with Dragons (2011), working to negotiate an alliance between the Night's Watch and the wildlings.</li>
      <li>Jon is a prominent point of view character in the novels, and has been called one of Martin's "finest creations".</li>
      <li>Jon Snow, born Aegon Targaryen, is the son of Lyanna Stark and Rhaegar Targaryen, the late Prince of Dragonstone</li>
      <li> Jon was born in 283 AC, near the end of Robert's Rebellion.</li>
      <li>Since he was young, Jon's hero was King Daeron, the Young Dragon, who had conquered Dorne at the age of fourteen.</li>
      <li>At the beginning of the story, Jon adopts the albino direwolf that he names Ghost. He later finds that at times he can "inhabit" the wolf and share its experiences.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
